<item>
            <title>[SPARK-27160] Incorrect Literal Casting of DecimalType in OrcFilters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-27160</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;DecimalType Literal should not be casted to Long.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;eg. For `df.filter(&quot;x &amp;lt; 3.14&quot;)`, assuming df (x in DecimalType) reads from a ORC table and uses the native ORC reader with predicate push down enabled, we will push down the `x &amp;lt; 3.14` predicate to the ORC reader via a SearchArgument.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OrcFilters will construct the SearchArgument, but not handle the DecimalType correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The previous impl will construct `x &amp;lt; 3` from `x &amp;lt; 3.14`.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
